diff:1619063019:1618104754:=62,75c62%0a%3c #foxbegin 210422-034339-303340#%0a%3c (:div1 class=expansionhead:)%0a%3c !!!Possible meaning of the a- prefix  %0a%3c -> - sgangu%0a%3c (:div1end:) %0a%3c >>messageitem%3c%3c %0a%3c It seems that this prefix can indicate being in the process of something or being in a particular state. In your example, you give the example "a-reading" which can imply that the person is currently in the process of reading. This same prefix can sometimes be added to adjectives to indicate that the adjective describes its noun in the present - such as in "the lantern is aglow". %0a%3c %0a%3c Source: %0a%3c https://www.englishclub.com/vocabulary/prefixes.htm%0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c >>%3c%3c%0a%3c #foxend 210422-034339-303340#%0a---%0a> %0a
