erb it prefixes to has a stressed first syllable. Additionally, the "a-" prefix normally does not appear before a verb which starts with a vowel sound.%0a%3c Ex: "They were a-conservin' their resources." and%0a%3c "The entire crowd started a-applaudin' after she performed." %0a%3c would not be well-formed.%0a%3c %0a%3c Interestingly, neither of these restrictions hold in Smoky Mountain English.%0a%3c %0a%3c Matyiku, Sabina. 2011. A-prefixing. Yale Grammatical Diversity Project: English in North America. (Available online at http://ygdp.yale.edu/phenomena/a-prefixing. Accessed on 2021-04-10). Updated by Tom McCoy (2015) and Katie Martin (2018).%0a%3c %0a%3c [[#contentends]]%0a%3c ----%0a%3c ----%0a%3c %0a%3c !!Expansions:%0a%3c [[#expansions]]%0a%3c %0a%3c [[#expansionsend]]%0a%3c %0a%3c ----%0a%3c %25red%25 '''Add an expansion:'''%0a%3c %0a%3c (:if [ exists GradebookExpansions.{$Name}-{$Author} || equal {$Author} {$:Author} ] :)%0a%3c %0a%3c (:else:)%0a%3c %0a%3c (:foxform Site.FoxForms#newexpansion:)%0a%3c %0a%3c (:ifend:)%0a%3c %0a%3c ----%0a%3c ----%0a%3c %0a%3c !!Comments%0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c (:section: F:)%0a%3c (:Category: MorphosyntacticDiversity:)%0a\ No newline at end of file%0a
